###
### Legends
### -------
###
### 1)  -a : input filename1 (backbone)
### 2)  -b : input filename2 (backbone)
### 3)  -d : description label in hdf5 file
### 4)  -t : no. of thermalization steps desired  (important for fast convergence)
### 5)  -s : no of skip steps desired    (important to keep autocorrelation low)
### 6)  -o : output filename
###

/Users/tamama/Programs/ALPS2/applications/qmc/lowa/merge_broken_timeseries_hdf5_measurements -a ./1/timeseries.mdns1 -b ./2/timeseries.mdns1 -o ./timeseries.mdns1 -d TimeSeries/Density/Set -t 10 -s 1
